## Don't

- Don't edit shipped Alembic migrations.
- Don't construct new `Settings()` instances.
- Don't call `litellm.completion` / `OllamaClient` directly.
- Don't write to Iceberg via raw PyIceberg.
- Don't pickle ORM objects across tasks (pass IDs, re-fetch).
- Don't put strategy logic in API routes.
- Don't break the progress-bus payload shape
  (`{task_id, stage, message, timestamp, **extras}`).
- Don't add new diagram formats. Mermaid only.
- Don't query Redis vector indexes directly. Use `HierarchicalRAG`.
- Don't write embeddings outside `aqp.rag.indexers.*`.
- Don't replace [aqp/data/chroma_store.py](mdc:aqp/data/chroma_store.py).
  Chroma stays for dataset/code metadata; Redis is the agent RAG.
- Don't mutate `agent_spec_versions` rows. They are immutable.
- Don't bypass `AgentRuntime.run` for spec-driven agents.
- Don't call `router_complete` from inside an agent body — declare the
  model in `AgentSpec.model`.
- Don't write decision/episode/reflection rows to Redis from agent
  code. Use `RedisHybridMemory` from
  [aqp/llm/memory.py](mdc:aqp/llm/memory.py).
- Don't bypass `BotRuntime` for bot lifecycle actions. Telemetry,
  `bot_versions` snapshots, and `bot_deployments` rows depend on it.
- Don't mutate `bot_versions` rows. They are immutable, hash-locked
  snapshots — re-snapshotting via
  [aqp/bots/registry.py::persist_spec](mdc:aqp/bots/registry.py)
  creates a new version row automatically.
- Don't put backtest / strategy / engine / agent logic inside a Bot
  subclass. Bots compose references and dispatch to existing primitives
  (`run_backtest_from_config`, `build_session_from_config`,
  `AgentRuntime`, `HierarchicalRAG`).
